# tariff_exposure2.py
"""
Production-grade tariff exposure estimator (proxy) + polished executive Excel.

Major upgrades vs earlier versions
----------------------------------
- Performance: vectorized keyword matching (compiled regex + str.contains) and vectorized text_blob build.
- Correctness: High scenario avoids double-counting via per-line MAX exposure fraction.
- Reporting quality: Vendor "parenting" (suffix stripping) for Top Suppliers rollups.
- Configurability: Optional heuristics JSON file to override keyword lists and vendor hint lists.
- Data quality controls: amount parse diagnostics, zero-spend rate, missing vendor rate, coverage check vs expected.
- Excel stability: no Excel "Tables" (prevents Excel Repair removal), safe filters + freeze panes.
- Excel robustness: strips illegal worksheet characters to prevent IllegalCharacterError.

Outputs
-------
outdir/
  tariff_executive_report.xlsx
  tariff_summary.json
  top_suppliers_base.csv
  top_categories_base.csv
  tariff_lines_scored.csv        (optional; can be very large)
  run_log.txt
"""

